@startuml
title D3 - Diagrama de Clases: Motor de Inferencia y Resultados

skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam linetype ortho

package "Evaluación Clínica" {

  class EvaluationClinical {
    +id: int
    +patient_id: int
    +user_id: int
    +reason: string
    +clinical_notes: string
    +status: string
    +created_at: datetime
  }

  class EvaluationClinicalFact {
    +id: int
    +evaluation_id: int
    +fact_key: string
    +fact_type: string
    +value: string
    +numeric_value: float
    +unit: string
  }
}

package "Motor de Inferencia" {

  class InferenceService {
    +process_evaluation(evaluation_id: int): List<InferenceResult>
    +combine_rule_and_bayes(rule_score: float, bayes_probability: float): float
    +persist_results(results: List): void
  }

  class InferenceEngine {
    +evaluate_rules(facts: List, rules: List<InferenceRule>): List<ConditionTrace>
    +calculate_rule_score(traces: List<ConditionTrace>): float
  }

  class ConditionEvaluator {
    +evaluate(condition: RuleCondition, facts: List): bool
    +compare(value: string, operator: string, expected: string): bool
  }

  class ConditionTrace {
    +rule_id: int
    +condition_key: string
    +expected_value: string
    +observed_value: string
    +operator: string
    +matched: bool
    +explanation: string
  }

  class BayesService {
    +calculate_probability(disease: Disease, facts: List): float
    +get_evidence_probabilities(disease_id: int): List<ClinicalProbability>
  }
}

package "Base de Conocimiento Usada por el Motor" {

  class Disease {
    +id: int
    +name: string
    +species_id: int
  }

  class ClinicalProbability {
    +id: int
    +disease_id: int
    +fact_key: string
    +probability: float
  }

  class RiskLevel {
    +id: int
    +name: string
    +priority: int
  }

  class InferenceRule {
    +id: int
    +name: string
    +disease_id: int
    +risk_level_id: int
    +weight: float
    +is_active: bool
  }

  class RuleCondition {
    +id: int
    +rule_id: int
    +fact_key: string
    +operator: string
    +expected_value: string
  }
}

package "Resultados Persistidos" {

  class InferenceResult {
    +id: int
    +evaluation_id: int
    +disease_id: int
    +risk_level_id: int
    +bayes_probability: float
    +rule_score: float
    +final_probability: float
    +diagnostic_suggestion: string
    +created_at: datetime
  }

  class ActivatedRule {
    +id: int
    +inference_result_id: int
    +rule_id: int
    +explanation: string
    +trace: json
  }
}

EvaluationClinical "1" -- "0..*" EvaluationClinicalFact : contiene
EvaluationClinical "1" -- "0..*" InferenceResult : genera

InferenceService ..> EvaluationClinical : obtiene evaluación
InferenceService ..> EvaluationClinicalFact : usa hechos clínicos
InferenceService ..> InferenceEngine : evalúa reglas
InferenceService ..> BayesService : calcula probabilidad
InferenceService ..> InferenceResult : persiste resultados
InferenceService ..> ActivatedRule : registra trazabilidad

InferenceEngine ..> InferenceRule : evalúa
InferenceEngine ..> RuleCondition : procesa condiciones
InferenceEngine ..> ConditionEvaluator : delega evaluación
InferenceEngine ..> ConditionTrace : genera trazas

ConditionEvaluator ..> RuleCondition : compara condición
ConditionEvaluator ..> EvaluationClinicalFact : contra hechos observados

BayesService ..> Disease : analiza enfermedad
BayesService ..> ClinicalProbability : consulta probabilidades

Disease "1" -- "0..*" InferenceRule : posee
Disease "1" -- "0..*" ClinicalProbability : probabilidades
InferenceRule "1" -- "1..*" RuleCondition : condiciones
RiskLevel "1" -- "0..*" InferenceRule : clasifica

Disease "1" -- "0..*" InferenceResult : resultado para
RiskLevel "1" -- "0..*" InferenceResult : nivel asignado
InferenceResult "1" -- "0..*" ActivatedRule : explica
InferenceRule "1" -- "0..*" ActivatedRule : fue activada

note right of InferenceService
Servicio orquestador del motor híbrido.

1. Obtiene los hechos clínicos.
2. Ejecuta reglas IF-THEN.
3. Calcula probabilidades con Naive Bayes.
4. Combina los resultados.
5. Persiste diagnóstico, riesgo y trazabilidad.
end note

note bottom of ActivatedRule
Permite explicar qué reglas fueron activadas
y por qué el sistema llegó a un resultado.
Esto aporta trazabilidad clínica.
end note

@enduml